===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[gee]] [[haw]] [[whimmy]] [[diddle]]}}

# A wooden [[toy]] consisting of a notched stick with a smaller stick attached on the end.  Rubbing the notched stick with another stick causes the smaller stick to [[spin]]; with practice the spin can be made to change from rightward ([[gee]]) to leftward ([[haw]]) and vice versa.
#*'''2002:''' Jeremy Gray, Jeff Davis, China Williams, ''Lonely Planet Georgia and the Carolinas'' [http://books.google.com/books?vid=ISBN1864503831&id=8lo41z8kowQC&pg=PA370&lpg=PA370&dq=%22gee+haw+whimmy+diddle%22&sig=ABC0l2lgYToCDAhJ2MbwHgxRI80]
#*:Here you can pick up mountain toys such as the ‘'''gee-haw whimmy diddle''',' a stick with a propeller that turns when you rub the notches on the stick.
#*'''2003:''' Darwin Porter, Danforth Prince, ''Frommer's The Carolinas and Georgia'' [http://books.google.com/books?vid=ISBN0764567535&id=QVutRQzsLmcC&pg=PA130&lpg=PA130&dq=%22gee-haw+whimmy+diddle%22&sig=bm9QR5JopEXGboGy5am_rnE4QC8]
#*:Special events at the FolkArt Center...include Fiber Day in May, the World '''Gee Haw Whimmy Diddle''' Competition in August...
#*'''2005:''' Martin Gardner, ''Smart Science Tricks'' [http://books.google.com/books?vid=ISBN1402722206&id=cCxPHCkQDJMC&pg=PA60&lpg=PA60&dq=%22gee+haw+whimmy+diddle%22&sig=qEwExzoHZHk59thd5g2Mc1o3TvA&hl=en]
#*:Thousands of wooden versions are sold each year, and a '''Gee Haw Whimmy Diddle''' Competition is held every summer at Asheville's Folk Art Center.

